Tens of families were left homeless after suspected hired goons demolished their houses in Kinangop, Nyandarua County. During the incident at Rwanyambo village in the area, the family of AIPCA head arch?bishop Fredrick Wang'ombe and twenty others were left counting losses of millions of shillings following the early morning demolition. At the center of controversy is a piece of land the bishop said was left to them by their parents but had been grabbed by influential people who had ordered that they be evicted.